## Round 2 — 2026-06-12 — review of v2 revision

Internal Claude red team (same three lenses), focused on whether the v2 fixes held.

### Reviewer A — Product Skeptic — convergence call: YES (advance)
- Fork A held but the rendering contract is a hidden behavioral promise P5 can't guarantee.
- Fork C is the strongest fix. Fork B coherent but "regenerated from claims" is unfalsifiable.
- **New contradiction (key):** auto-merge (P1) + trusted-only synthesis (P7) means a brand-new
  subject's first report synthesizes from ZERO trusted claims — the cold-start case §1 promises to
  serve. Gating created this; v1 didn't have it.
- Also: P7 has no promotion *trigger* (corroboration only arrives on later runs; nothing triggers
  re-research) — "the accumulation flywheel has no motor." Single-researcher + subscription ToS
  caps the wedge. Domain-profile bias named but unowned.
- **Single highest-value change:** define what a first-run report on a brand-new subject
  synthesizes from.

### Reviewer B — Technical Realist — convergence call: YES (advance)
- Fork A holds technically. Fork B inconsistent: prose→claims→prose is NOT identity-preserving
  (extraction is lossy); "regenerated" prose is a thinner artifact — say "claims-derived view."
- **Fork C's gate has no feasible promotion signal:** P7 promotes on corroboration, but P4 concedes
  corroboration can't detect independence and is "a weak signal." So promotion is either inflatable
  (defeats the gate) or reduces to single-source-trust + no-contradiction. v2 never picks. The gate
  is called "primary defense" while its main signal is conceded unsound — the central gap.
- **New contradiction:** "provisional excluded from synthesis" (P7) vs "conflict surfaced inline in
  prose" (P5) — a fresh contradicting claim is provisional, so is it excluded or surfaced?
- Cold-start: trusted-by-default makes first reports empty — early value is *negative*.
- **Single highest-value change:** define the promotion signal — e.g. promote = (source-trust ≥ bar)
  AND (no open contradiction), corroboration explicitly NOT an input until independence lands; and
  state whether provisional contradicting claims surface in prose.

### Reviewer C — Market Cynic — convergence call: NO
- §7 names the "why switch" question then declines to answer it; the wedge loses to Elicit (rigor)
  and ChatGPT-memory (low-effort recall). The defensible sliver — cross-run conflict/confidence
  state — is exactly what Fork A defers (no UI to see it).
- **Fork A guts the v1 product:** v1 ships "a schema plus a ⚠ string in prose" — "a database
  migration wearing a vision's clothes." Fork C adds friction with no v1 payoff (thinner reports).
- No single-session "aha"; audit dependency unfunded; target persona unspecified for GTM.
- **Single highest-value change:** pull ONE read-only surface into v1 — a `dossier show <subject>`
  render of trusted claims, open conflicts, and confidence tiers — so the wedge is testable in the
  first session, not a deferred promise.

