## Round 4 — 2026-06-12 — final verification of v4

Final check. Tally with external CLIs: **4 ADVANCE / 1 ANOTHER ROUND**.

- **Product skeptic — ADVANCE.** All five v4 fixes (a)-(e) hold; no fix reopened a prior issue.
- **Technical realist — ADVANCE.** Each fix holds logically; (b)'s carve-out reinforces immutability.
- **Market cynic — ADVANCE.** §7 wedge intact and tightened; de-tautologized §3 now measures the
  wedge rather than restating it; no new GTM contradiction.
- **gemini — ADVANCE.** Structural and terminology convergence reached.
- **codex — ANOTHER ROUND (single sharp objection):** v4 fix (d) "DOESN'T HOLD" — degraded-synthesis
  caveats mark *provisional* content, so they cannot backstop an undetected contradiction that
  *over-promotes* a claim to trusted (such a claim renders trusted/uncaveated). Only audit (and later
  detection→demotion) does. **Valid.**

### Disposition (v5)
codex is right. Fixed in v5: P7 now separates the two failure modes — over-promotion is backstopped
by after-the-fact audit and later contradiction-detection→demotion (NOT caveats); caveats backstop
the distinct degraded-synthesis (thin-trusted-base) case. This directly closes the only remaining
objection. **Convergence reached across all reviewers** — remaining items are deferred Architecture
concerns, not vision-level issues.

