## Round 5 — 2026-06-12 — re-review of the v6 fact-base reframe

Internal Claude red team. Tally with external CLIs so far: **0 ADVANCE / 4 ANOTHER ROUND** (gemini pending).

### Reviewer A — Product Skeptic — ANOTHER ROUND
- P5 strains: a fact carries as-of date/scope qualifiers (§5), so France pop 68.2M(2023) vs 67.9M(2021)
  is NOT a conflict — two valid time-points. P5's "different value = conflict" is under-specified.
- P4 strain: per-(type,property) trust matrix is heavier than v5's per-source prior.
- New problems: (a) non-scalar facts (relationships, multi-valued like official languages, time-series)
  — model assumes a scalar "value"; a multi-valued property looks like perpetual self-conflict;
  (b) properties contested in *definition* not value (accuracy depends on dataset/metric); (c) entities
  that don't cleanly instance (methods/events/concepts vs France/aspirin) — slug-keying a fuzzy entity
  is an unearned vision claim; (d) "physical world" over-narrows and fights its own ML example.
- **Blocker:** the fact model is silently scalar-only; non-scalar + definitional disagreement are
  vision-level gaps, not deferrable detail.

### Reviewer B — Technical Realist — ANOTHER ROUND
- Reframe makes the data model MORE coherent ((instance,property) gives P6 a real primary key).
- Risk claim (i) **partially true, overstated**: narrows the schema/grammar, but value/unit fidelity,
  qualifier capture, and as-of date — the hard part — survive inside the triple. Restate as "narrows
  schema, not semantic-fidelity risk."
- Risk claim (ii) **true with correctly-scoped residual**, but understates multi-valued properties
  (half-life by route/dose) and as-of dating — real key is (instance, property, as-of).
- New: value-equality with tolerance + unit normalization is a NEW conflict-detection primitive
  (68.2M vs 68,200,000 vs 68.15M); time-varying facts make "conflict vs newer vs staleness" first-class.
- **Blocker:** restate claim (i); define value-equality/unit-normalization as the new conflict primitive.

### Reviewer C — Market Cynic — ANOTHER ROUND
- Wedge framing marginally stronger (drops the Elicit fight) but moat weaker: the differentiator is a
  feature layer, not a defensible asset; Wikidata has data+community, LLM-with-search gives it free.
- "Personal Wikidata" is a category people avoid (cf. manual spreadsheets never disrupted); facts are
  a commodity LLMs give free; cross-source conflict matters to a tiny high-stakes slice who also
  distrust auto-extraction — and v1 defers interactive adjudication.
- **Blocker:** demand for an auto-built conflict-aware fact base is unvalidated; §7's own hedge admits
  the wedge isn't yet defensible.

### External codex — ANOTHER ROUND
- P5 manufactures conflicts (variance by date/scope/method/uncertainty); P6 conflates independent
  source assertions with genuine temporal change; P7 "no open contradiction" becomes hostile to
  measured facts (legitimate variance blocks/demotes trust); "physical world" doesn't cohere with the
  accuracy example. Both risk-reduction claims **refuted** as written (qualifier-aware assertion
  identity is the real problem, not (instance,property)).
- **Blocker:** qualifier-aware assertion identity and conflict semantics are foundational, but v6
  treats (instance, property) as sufficient.

### Synthesis direction
The reframe is sound in spirit but v6 under-modeled facts. Convergent fixes: (1) **qualifier-aware
fact identity** — key includes as-of date / scope / method, so differing-qualifier values are distinct
facts, not conflicts; (2) distinguish **conflict vs. temporal-change vs. multi-valued**; define
**value-equality + unit normalization** as the conflict primitive; (3) **restate risk-reduction claim
(i)** honestly (schema not semantics); (4) **broaden/clarify the framing** beyond "physical world";
(5) confront the **demand** challenge via a concrete high-stakes persona. (1)-(4) are vision edits;
(5) is the next Feature-Spec gate.

