## Round 6 — 2026-06-12 — re-convergence check on v7

Internal Claude red team + external CLIs. Tally: **4 ADVANCE / 1 ANOTHER ROUND** (codex; fixed in v8).

- **Product skeptic — ADVANCE.** All five round-5 blockers CLOSED; no surviving new contradiction;
  verified examples don't smuggle multi-valued/time-series facts.
- **Technical realist — ADVANCE.** Blockers closed at vision/logic level; the residual (P5/P7 hinge on
  the deferred value-equality + qualifier-alignment primitive) is an owned Architecture dependency,
  honestly flagged, not a contradiction.
- **Market cynic — ADVANCE.** Demand blocker CLOSED at vision level (honest, high-stakes, falsifiable).
  Flagged a Feature-Spec tension: high-stakes users must *act* on conflicts but v1 is read-only;
  "competitive/market intelligence" is the softest of the named domains. (→ deferred items #31, #32.)
- **gemini — ADVANCE.** All five closed; two flagged issues (single-valued forcing false conflicts on
  lists; qualifier-alignment failure → over-promotion) — both addressed by v8.
- **codex — ANOTHER ROUND (valid, fixed in v8):** v7's "single value per (instance, property,
  qualifiers)" contradicted the conflict model (a conflict needs ≥2 unequal values under that exact
  key); revision-vs-concurrent-assertion also blurred.

### Disposition (v8)
codex's contradiction fixed: **provenance is part of fact identity** — each fact is one source's
assertion, so a qualified key carries multiple competing source-assertions (the conflict), while the
dossier presents one *resolved current* value. Clarified revision (one source over time) vs. conflict
(different sources), and intrinsic multi-valued properties vs. cross-source disagreement; sharpened
P7's over-promotion dependency to name qualifier under-/over-matching (gemini). **Reframe converged.**

